[SN]TITLE[SN]
Underley Hall School abuse probe: Five men charged

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Five men have been charged with assault at a school for young people with behavioural problems.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The offences are said to have taken place at Underley Hall School, near Kirkby Lonsdale in Cumbria, which closed in 2012.
It follows the launch of Operation Tweed in 2014 by Cumbria Police after a former pupil made allegations.
Those charged - aged between 57 and 72 - will appear at South Cumbria Magistrates Court on 15 February.
They are:
??         Errol Mayer, 72, of New Road, Kirkby Lonsdale - 18 counts of assault ABH and 10 charges of child cruelty
??         John Studley, 64, of Maryland Close, Silverdale, Lancashire - one count of assault ABH
??         Frederick Taylor, 74, of Lower Park Royd Drive, Sowerby Bridge, West Yorkshire - one count of assault ABH
??         James Farish, 57, of Oakwood, Kendal - one count of assault ABH
??         David Hadwin, 70, of Raygarth Road, Kirkby Lonsdale - one count of assault ABH
